# graphify knowledge graph — local build artifact, entirely untracked.
# Build it with `graphify update .` (AST only, seconds, no API cost). The semantic layer
# needs an LLM and is not reproducible without one; see CLAUDE.md for how to get it back.
# We used to track graph.json so a clone could inherit that layer, but the post-commit
# hook rebuilds without a key and the rebuild is lossy, so tracking eroded the layer a
# commit at a time and charged ~27k lines of diff for the privilege.
/graphify-out/
